float pupilDiameter ( int  eye_id  )  const

The diameter of the pupil (in metres).

This value is only available if the corresponding Gaze Quality Level for this frame is 3.

Parameters:
eye_id he eye to retrieve the pupil diameter for (either sm::eod::RIGHT_EYE or sm::eod::LEFT_EYE)
Precondition:
eye_id is either sm::eod::LEFT_EYE or sm::eod::RIGHT_EYE

const fStdVector3& pupilPosition ( int  eye_id  )  const

Positions of the centre of the pupils in world coordinates.

The positions of the centre of the pupils in world coordinates is derived directly from the images by localising the iris in both images and triangulation. It is independent from eye ball calibration. This parameter was added for people who need to know the position of the pupils in space, i.e. for 3D displays. The values are unfiltered image processing results.

Parameters:
eye_id The eye to retrieve the pupil position for (either sm::eod::RIGHT_EYE or sm::eod::LEFT_EYE)
Precondition:
eye_id is either sm::eod::LEFT_EYE or sm::eod::RIGHT_EYE
